19:28.827 --> 19:32.754
The live filter, because fantasy is the new reality.

19:37.922 --> 19:39.544
So my wife, Kelly, and I have four kids.

19:39.925 --> 19:44.732
And when they were younger, we decided that we're going to make a really particularly fascinating Easter memory.

19:44.792 --> 19:48.678
So we went out and bought this special 3D bunny cake from William Sonoma.

19:48.698 --> 19:54.928
And I don't know if you've ever seen these, but the cake pan actually allows you to make both halves of a bunny that's life size.

19:55.048 --> 19:58.353
And when you make it correctly, you seal them together with frosting.

19:58.413 --> 20:03.781
It sits upright and then you frost it and you put jelly beans on the eyeballs and it looks like it's something that came out of the catalog.

20:03.801 --> 20:06.866
Well, I followed the directions as best I knew how.

20:07.042 --> 20:11.992
made both halves of the bunny, sealed it with frosting, sitting upright on the counter, looks golden.

20:12.593 --> 20:13.755
And then we start to frost it.

20:14.517 --> 20:17.563
And the white frosting is buttercream, so we know it's gonna be delectable.

20:17.623 --> 20:21.330
But as we're going on, we noticed that it's starting to pull the bunny

20:21.986 --> 20:23.228
like a part in halves.

20:23.248 --> 20:24.190
And we're like, well, that's not great.

20:24.210 --> 20:26.774
So we slather a little bit more on it.

20:26.834 --> 20:30.380
We get the frosting all on the ears and the face and everything's just how we want it.

20:30.420 --> 20:38.454
And then we stand back to kind of like appreciate it in all of its glory and majesty and are slightly concerned when we see the bunny's head start to bow.

20:38.474 --> 20:48.210
And imagine our horror when we see it start to crack right at the base of its neck and then under the weight of its own frosting, the bunny's head falls off.

20:48.738 --> 20:58.911
And something that was supposed to be this magical Easter memory turned into the stuff of comical nightmares because there's a beheaded bunny on the Easter kitchen counter.

20:58.931 --> 21:06.340
Now, sometimes you follow the directions exactly as you were told and things don't turn out the way that you want them to.

21:06.360 --> 21:08.823
And sometimes it's a fun and hilarious family memory.

21:09.704 --> 21:11.186
But sometimes the stakes are a little bit higher.

21:12.194 --> 21:25.068
Sometimes you follow all the instructions, the way that you thought that you should, to get a ideal image, a picture-perfect Instagram-friendly family, and things don't turn out exactly the way that you'd hoped.

21:25.088 --> 21:37.842
And we're gonna look at a passage of scripture today that tells us a story of a family that experiences that, heartbreak, disillusionment, disappointment, and how they learn to trust God in the midst of all of that, and how maybe we can too.

21:38.914 --> 21:42.558
About 3,500 years ago, the people of Israel are living in chaos.

21:43.378 --> 21:47.302
Their ancestors have been let out of slavery in Egypt by Moses into the Promised Land.

21:48.183 --> 21:50.025
But it doesn't take long for them to lose their way.

21:50.065 --> 21:56.271
And as a consequence, God allows the neighboring countries and armies to invade and oppress them.

21:57.032 --> 22:04.259
And when the people get desperate, they cry out to the Lord for help and he sends a judge or a ruler or a savior to come and help them.

22:04.279 --> 22:06.802
We pick up the story here in Judges chapter 13.

22:07.746 --> 22:10.189
Again, the Israelites did evil in the eyes of the Lord.

22:11.111 --> 22:13.995
So the Lord delivered them into the hands of the Philistines for 40 years.

22:15.397 --> 22:22.426
A certain man from Zora named Minoa from the clan of the Danites had a wife who was childless, unable to give birth.

22:23.608 --> 22:30.197
The angel of the Lord appeared to her and said, you are barren and childless, but you are going to become pregnant and give birth to a son.

22:30.257 --> 22:36.786
Now see to it that you drink no wine or other fermented drink and that you do not eat anything unclean.

22:37.826 --> 22:45.354
You will become pregnant and have a son whose head is never to be touched by a razor because the boy is to be a Nazaret dedicated to God from the womb.

22:46.415 --> 22:49.538
He will take the lead in delivering Israel from the hands of the Philistines.

22:50.479 --> 22:51.740
We jump ahead to verse 24.

22:52.901 --> 22:55.084
The woman gave birth to a boy named Samson.

22:55.724 --> 23:02.992
He grew and the Lord blessed him and the spirit of the Lord began to stir in him when he was in Mahana Dan between Zora and Esther Olm.

23:03.752 --> 23:05.394
I'm gonna skip forward to chapter 14.

23:06.210 --> 23:11.137
Samson, now a young man, went down to Timna and saw there a young Philistine woman.

23:12.058 --> 23:18.367
When he returned, he said to his father and mother, I have seen a Philistine woman in Timna, now get her for me as my wife.

23:20.310 --> 23:26.759
His father and mother replied, isn't there an acceptable woman among your relatives or among all our people?

23:27.179 --> 23:30.264
Must you go to the uncircumstised Philistines to get a wife?

23:31.645 --> 23:33.728
But Samson said to his father, get her for me.

23:33.929 --> 23:34.930
She's the right one for me.

23:35.746 --> 23:47.040
And then in parentheses, the author says, his parents did not know that this was from the Lord, who was seeking an occasion to confront the Philistines, for at that time they were ruling over Israel.

23:47.741 --> 23:48.942
So we'll skip ahead in the story a little bit.

23:48.982 --> 23:52.386
Samson goes down to Timna for his version of a Philistine bachelor party.

23:53.007 --> 24:00.416
The village selects 30 men to be his groomsmen, and he gives them a riddle for them to answer by the end of the seven day festival.

24:00.717 --> 24:05.042
He says, hey, if you can solve my riddle, I will give each one of you your own set of clothes.

24:05.410 --> 24:08.714
But if you can't solve the riddle, all of you owe me a set of clothes.

24:08.734 --> 24:11.538
So either I'll give you 30 garments or you'll give me 30 garments.

24:11.858 --> 24:13.520
You got seven days, game on.

24:14.281 --> 24:19.508
Well, they get four days into the festival and the guys are at their wits and they can't solve the riddle to save their lives.

24:20.349 --> 24:31.464
So they lean on Samson's new bride, a woman that they have grown up with, probably known her since childhood and say, give us a secret to the riddle or we'll burn your father's house down with you in it.

24:31.484 --> 24:33.426
So it's the most severe threat that they can make.

24:34.562 --> 24:38.186
So she tries to kind of weasel the answer out of Samson.

24:38.367 --> 24:42.532
And like at the last minute, on the morning of the seventh day, he shares it with her.

24:42.812 --> 24:44.093
She shares it with the groomsmen.

24:44.554 --> 24:50.461
And they give Samson the right answer just as the clock is running down sunset on the seventh day.

24:52.724 --> 24:57.449
Then the scriptures say this, then the spirit of the Lord came powerfully upon Samson.

24:57.550 --> 25:01.234
And he went down to Ashguan, a town about 20 miles away.

25:01.474 --> 25:06.647
struck down 30 of their men, stripped them of everything, and gave their clothes to those who had explained the riddle.

25:07.248 --> 25:16.430
Burning with anger, he returned to his father's home, and Samson's wife was given to one of his companions who had attended him at the feast.

25:16.451 --> 25:19.538
So imagine that you were Samson's mother and father.

25:20.322 --> 25:27.660
You've struggled for years to be able to conceive, and when you finally do, you get this miracle baby, and you have checked every box that God asked you to check.

25:27.680 --> 25:31.890
She didn't consume any alcohol when he was in utero, and a razor's never

25:32.034 --> 25:32.675
touched his head.

25:32.695 --> 25:35.618
They're doing everything that they have received through divine instructions.

25:36.138 --> 25:49.512
And then when he's finally able to come of age and make his own choices, he horrifies them by saying, I wanna marry somebody that I've never even had a full conversation with, somebody I'm just like viscerally attracted to and she's not a member of our tribe.

25:49.572 --> 25:55.978
She doesn't share our God, she doesn't share our values, she doesn't share our commitment to character, she doesn't share our heritage.

25:57.099 --> 25:59.922
And you just have to imagine that something snaps

26:00.546 --> 26:04.670
in Samson's parents to be able to say, God, where did we go wrong?

26:05.551 --> 26:07.333
This isn't what we wanted for him.

26:07.373 --> 26:09.315
This isn't what we wanted for our town.

26:09.355 --> 26:11.277
This isn't what we wanted for us as a family.

26:12.258 --> 26:15.281
God, what is going on and what would you have us do?

26:16.642 --> 26:23.029
And I believe that Samson's parents kind of give us a blueprint or a template for how to proceed.

26:23.089 --> 26:27.954
We don't get the full detail of what's going on behind the scenes, but I'm gonna speculate a little bit

26:28.258 --> 26:36.350
and see if we can have three steps that we can take when our blueprints for our family get interrupted.

26:36.891 --> 26:47.967
And I believe that the first step is this, that when things don't go the way that we had hoped, that we grieve the loss, that the first step in dealing with that disappointment is leaning into the hurt.

26:47.987 --> 26:55.378
Anytime there's a loss in our family, whether it's a loss of relationship, the loss of a dream, or the loss of a loved one,

26:55.842 --> 26:58.465
We enter into this wrestling match with grief.

26:59.726 --> 27:04.071
I used to think that grief was linear, that there was just, you know, you went through the stages one at a time.

27:05.132 --> 27:10.858
But I had a friend who had gone through a heartbreaking loss of losing his wife and the mother of their children at a very young age to cancer.

27:10.898 --> 27:20.749
And he said, Steve, grief is like getting dropped into the middle of a forest and having to find your way out without any help.

27:20.769 --> 27:22.371
Grief can be strangely disorienting.

27:22.911 --> 27:25.394
But the one comfort that we have in the scriptures is that

27:25.506 --> 27:29.129
Families have been dealing with disappointment, grief, and loss for centuries.

27:30.291 --> 27:34.575
And what I love about the scriptures is that in the Psalms, we have these Psalms of lament.

27:34.635 --> 27:39.059
These songs where people cry out to God and say, this God, this isn't the way that it was supposed to be.

27:39.119 --> 27:41.381
Will you intervene?

27:41.421 --> 27:42.382
Will you give us comfort?

27:42.422 --> 27:43.784
Will you give us hope?

27:43.824 --> 27:49.329
Will you give us any shred of the future that we can hang on to in the midst of our disillusionment?

27:50.750 --> 27:52.772
There's an author by the name of Susan David.

27:52.812 --> 27:54.674
She wrote a book called Emotional Agility.

27:55.554 --> 28:03.184
She talked about how when her son was an infant, she took him to the pediatrician's office and for a vaccination, they gave him a needle poke in his heel.

28:03.464 --> 28:05.587
And she said, immediately he began to wail.

28:06.528 --> 28:11.614
And she goes instinctively, as a mother, I held him close and I just started to pat him and say, it's okay, it's okay.

28:13.056 --> 28:21.106
And she said, a very wise nurse came up and said this to me, it's not okay, but it will be.

28:23.106 --> 28:28.312
Being able to grieve as a family allows us to actually speak pain out loud and say, what's happening right now?

28:28.733 --> 28:29.574
Is it what we'd hope for?

28:29.694 --> 28:30.795
It hurts terribly.

28:31.676 --> 28:35.421
It doesn't mean that God can't redeem it in time, but we can't skip steps.

28:36.142 --> 28:40.006
We have to acknowledge what has been lost in this moment and lean into it.

28:41.248 --> 28:49.618
Pete Doctor, who directed some really incredible Pixar films, especially like the newly released Soul, talked about shooting the movie Inside Out.

28:49.858 --> 28:56.988
And he said initially that movie was supposed to be a dance between joy and fear, but the final version was kind of a dance between joy and sorrow.

28:57.028 --> 29:00.352
And he said, sorrow is the listening emotion.

29:00.372 --> 29:08.543
When we experience sorrow, it prompts us to listen to one another and find out where the source of that hurt is coming from.

29:10.847 --> 29:12.869
There's nothing worse than watching our kids hurt.

29:14.211 --> 29:19.218
And because my children's pain is painful to watch, I'm always tempted to fast forward through it.

29:19.970 --> 29:24.538
But if I do that, I miss out on the lessons that God wants to teach me and them in the process.

29:26.220 --> 29:42.227
Almost exactly four years ago, our family relocated from suburban Detroit, where Kelly and I had been married, where every single one of our kids had been born, where we built some amazing friendships, where we were part of incredible church, and felt like God was prompting us to move to the other side of the state, to the Grand Rapids area.

29:42.608 --> 29:44.050
And it was a move that we made in faith.

29:44.898 --> 29:59.338
And we knew that it would kind of sting to be uprooted and relocated, but we had no idea how deeply we would grieve and mourn the loss of some of those relationships and some of the comforts and some of the stability that we had in that environment.

29:59.939 --> 30:14.098
And when my kids, especially my oldest daughter, who we moved right between seventh and eighth grade, a tough season of anybody's life by any imagination, but was compounded by the fact that we moved her in the middle of middle school and to watch her struggle.

30:14.818 --> 30:20.926
to find friends, to find community, to find identity, to find purpose was heartbreaking for me.

30:21.487 --> 30:25.072
And as a dad, I just wanted to skip all the way through it.

30:26.414 --> 30:36.568
But God's been teaching me to slow down and say, it's okay to sit and weep together as a family and say, this wasn't what we'd hoped for, but we believe that God is gonna meet us in it.

30:36.588 --> 30:40.914
So that first step is to acknowledge that grieving

30:42.018 --> 30:45.061
is a discipline, it's a practice that we can learn together as a family.

30:45.081 --> 30:48.906
And the scriptures give us great permission that it was something that Jesus did as well.

30:50.027 --> 30:55.813
We read in John chapter 11, when Jesus' friend Lazarus died, he wept with Lazarus' family.

30:56.975 --> 31:01.580
And when our family hurts, there's comfort in knowing that Jesus weeps with us too.

31:04.783 --> 31:10.930
So if you feel like your family dream or agenda has jumped the reals, we can start by grieving the laws.

31:11.682 --> 31:14.206
And then we proceed by praying for protection.

31:15.487 --> 31:20.514
In the early years of our parenting, we've got this advantage where we can manipulate the variables in our child's lives.

31:21.175 --> 31:22.978
We've got car seats and we've got seat belts.

31:23.278 --> 31:25.742
We can determine when and where they play outside.

31:26.122 --> 31:29.307
But as kids get older, it's harder and harder to do.

31:29.347 --> 31:40.082
Now, you still might have like middle school and high school tracking abilities if you have apps like Life360, but just because you know where they are doesn't mean that you know exactly what they're doing.

31:41.538 --> 31:44.822
And I wonder if Samson's parents were praying for him.

31:46.544 --> 31:50.650
Because Samson was physically strong, there wasn't a threat that he faced externally.

31:50.990 --> 31:53.573
Samson's greatest danger was himself.

31:53.653 --> 31:56.737
And maybe that's what his parents were praying, that he would be protected from himself.

31:57.138 --> 31:59.220
Because Samson clearly has impulse control issues.

31:59.661 --> 32:01.624
We see it when he tracks down his fiancee.

32:01.944 --> 32:04.347
We see it when he connects with a prostitute in Gaza.

32:04.367 --> 32:09.874
We see it in this famous encounter that he has with another woman who ultimately does not have his best interests in mind.

32:10.018 --> 32:11.600
a woman by the name of Delilah.

32:12.742 --> 32:21.175
And I remember when I was growing up, I'm the fifth of six kids, that one of my dad's great prayers is that God would protect us from ourselves.

32:22.257 --> 32:33.074
I had an older sister who, this isn't like pre-cell phone days, she was on a date that went so badly that she jumped out of a moving van and walked to a pay phone, borrow a quarter and call my dad to come and pick her up.

32:34.146 --> 32:45.577
So by the time my parents got to my sister and I, the youngest of the six kids, their anxiety level had kind of been through the wringer for their kids' emotional, spiritual, psychological safety.

32:46.678 --> 32:51.844
And I remember one night, very vividly, I was an upperclassman, probably a junior or senior in high school.

32:51.864 --> 32:58.750
I had come home after a late night with friends and opened the front door to the left of our front door as our living room and to the right as a stair.

32:58.811 --> 33:02.354
So if you're gonna go up to the bedrooms, you kind of had to come through that path.

33:03.810 --> 33:14.646
And I'll never forget, look into my left and seeing my father asleep on his knees with a blanket and an open Bible.

33:16.829 --> 33:26.002
Praying for the one variable that he couldn't control, which was the choices that his almost adult children were making that he couldn't protect them from.

33:27.202 --> 33:31.126
And God doesn't promise that all of our kids will be spared from heartache.

33:31.166 --> 33:34.370
God doesn't promise that our families will get to bypass disappointment.

33:35.431 --> 33:50.128
But I do believe that God invites us to the point of prayer so that we can be surrendered and we can be present with God in the dreams and the hurts and the desires that we have for our children, their choices and their wellbeing.

33:52.390 --> 33:55.954
So when you're praying, pray that God will protect your kids, not just from physical harm,

33:56.226 --> 34:03.776
Maybe from themselves, pray that God would protect them from despair, and pray that God would protect you from fear.

34:04.618 --> 34:12.388
Because I've learned the hard way in my own parenting, that when I'm operating out of fear, I tend to lead my family out of fear and manipulation.

34:12.749 --> 34:16.113
I try to shame my kids towards a particular set of outcomes.

34:16.894 --> 34:17.635
It doesn't honor them.

34:17.655 --> 34:18.497
It doesn't serve them.

34:18.877 --> 34:19.838
It doesn't love them well.

34:21.300 --> 34:25.426
But love, scriptures tell us that perfect love drives out all fear.

34:26.530 --> 34:32.338
And love pushes us towards kindness and grace and truth and patience.

34:33.600 --> 34:38.787
So if it starts to feel like things are unraveling, it's okay to pause and grieve whatever it is that you've lost.

34:40.249 --> 34:46.738
It's also important that we pray for protection for our minds, for our hearts, our spirits, our bodies and our unity.

34:47.719 --> 34:53.688
And then finally, it's critical that we stop to ask God for insight to pray this prayer.

34:53.728 --> 34:55.410
God, will you please show me

34:55.618 --> 34:56.499
what I can't see.

34:57.401 --> 35:07.335
I love that the author of Judges put that parenthetical note in the middle of Samson's story to say, Samson was making a choice that his parents didn't like, didn't approve of, and didn't understand.

35:08.296 --> 35:23.378
But God had the 30,000 foot view of that whole situation and knew that God was allowing an inappropriate desire on Samson's part to lead him into a set of circumstances that would allow God to get glory and the people of Israel to experience freedom.

35:23.842 --> 35:31.734
And although Samson kind of dove headlong into that relationship, hoping that it would be a lifelong run, it only ended up being a seven-day marriage.

35:32.735 --> 35:41.468
And Samson experienced heartache on the tail end of that, but even so, God protected him from longer-term consequences of that particular situation.

35:44.513 --> 35:50.962
Some of the prayers that we pray for our families might not get answered for days, months, or even years,

35:51.810 --> 35:56.157
But sometimes our kids become the answers to the prayers that we're praying for them.

35:57.359 --> 36:01.245
I remember one time I was tucking my children in to bed at night.

36:02.187 --> 36:05.892
And Kellen, I try to be mindful and strategic in the names that we gave them.

36:05.953 --> 36:07.415
So our oldest daughter is Grace.

36:07.455 --> 36:14.166
And so when we tuck her in, we say, hey God, thank you for Grace, our precious gift, because the Greek word for Grace also means gift.

36:14.186 --> 36:19.474
And then when we tuck in Naomi, our second born, we're reminded of the story of Naomi, the Bible, who was a bridge builder.

36:19.810 --> 36:20.512
And we tuck her in.

36:20.532 --> 36:21.936
We say, Hey, God, please be with Naomi.

36:21.956 --> 36:27.089
Make her a brave friend and make Josiah a strong king and make Mariam a freedom song.

36:27.130 --> 36:30.298
And one particular night, I was tucking my son into bed.

36:30.358 --> 36:36.274
And as I was walking out the door, he goes, Hey, dad, who tells you who you are?

36:39.522 --> 36:49.152
And it hit me like a dagger because I had been going through a particularly challenging season at work where I felt like my performance and my identity and my character and my competence were all being called into question.

36:49.692 --> 37:07.090
And in that one split second of a completely ordinary in routine exercise, God used the faith and the insight and the wisdom of my son to give me clarity to be able to say like, I needed to be on my knees before God so that I would allow God to remind me who he says that I am.

37:07.714 --> 37:14.683
and not allowing culture or society or strangers or social media or even my place of work to define my identity.

37:16.685 --> 37:21.391
Sometimes our kids will push us to believe things that we're not ready to believe.

37:22.272 --> 37:31.023
I told you before that we were prayerfully considering this move where we would kind of turn away from everything that we had kind of come to know as a family and start from scratch.

37:31.704 --> 37:36.210
And that time my daughter who was, I believe she was like 11 at the time,

37:36.290 --> 37:39.674
Even when I was struggling, I go, hey, Naomi, what do you think about this decision?

37:39.734 --> 37:43.660
And she, without flinching, she goes, I think God is leading us on a new adventure.

37:45.202 --> 37:54.774
And sometimes our kids are the breath of faith and fresh air and enthusiasm that we need to take the next step that we need to take as a family.

37:54.794 --> 38:01.042
And then sometimes the things that feel like heartache on the front end end up being wisdom or even protection on the tail end.

38:01.954 --> 38:05.800
About five years ago, I had interviewed for a job at a dream organization.

38:05.860 --> 38:12.030
In fact, I had like such an infatuation with them vocationally that I think I had interviewed for five different jobs over the course of 10 years.

38:12.391 --> 38:14.474
You would have thought I would have got the hit that God didn't want me there.

38:14.574 --> 38:18.901
But on this one particular round, I interviewed for a job, got turned down again.

38:18.921 --> 38:27.154
And my wife, Kelly, just in a voice of great gentle truths, she goes, Steve, I just have this gnawing sense that God is protecting us from something.

38:28.066 --> 38:33.314
And I was like, I can't imagine in a thousand years what we would need to be protected from in a dream scenario like that.

38:34.476 --> 38:44.592
And sure enough, just a few years after I'd had that interview, a major kind of organizational tidal wave hit that organization that forced them to lay a number of people off.

38:44.612 --> 38:51.282
And Kelly's gut instinct or her sense of being able to kind of align her understanding and wisdom with the Holy Spirit was dead on.

38:51.970 --> 38:59.378
And sometimes we can't see how in the short term, God is protecting us from something that could be ultimately destructive for us in the long term.

39:01.641 --> 39:17.659
When I was kind of at that crossroads with our family, because I had been kind of, in my own mind, locked into the sense that we were in our dream house and our dream scenario and we were just gonna kind of graduate every kid from that home into this high school district and we would retire there.

39:17.679 --> 39:20.402
And when that didn't happen, I was just, I was really rattled.

39:20.898 --> 39:24.001
And I remember sitting down with a friend praying about whether or not we should make this move.

39:24.021 --> 39:28.626
And he goes, Steve, it sounds like you're having a kind of a need to have an honest conversation with God.

39:30.087 --> 39:34.812
And he goes, so it sounds like you just need to sit down and confess your greatest fear to God.

39:35.933 --> 39:37.755
And I said, this guy's name was Jamie.

39:37.775 --> 39:39.557
I go, Jamie, I don't need to tell God what I'm feeling.

39:39.577 --> 39:40.258
God already knows.

39:40.278 --> 39:41.519
He goes, well, you don't need to tell it for God.

39:41.539 --> 39:42.480
You need to say it for you.

39:43.741 --> 39:48.626
So I remember sitting in the balcony of this chapel, in this padded pew,

39:50.306 --> 39:59.935
In a moment of kind of total desperation, I opened up my hands and I said, God, I confess that I don't trust you with my kids.

39:59.955 --> 40:01.797
And then Jamie said, well, let me ask you a follow up question.

40:01.857 --> 40:02.277
Why not?

40:03.238 --> 40:07.823
And I said, because God at my core, I don't believe that you love them as much as I do.

40:08.784 --> 40:12.968
And as soon as those words rolled out of my mouth, it was like a, it was like a damn broken term.

40:14.469 --> 40:19.634
And I felt like God was able to say, Steve, they are mine before they are yours.

40:20.898 --> 40:31.510
even though this isn't the season that you would have chosen for your family doesn't mean that I'm not in it and doesn't mean that I won't redeem it doesn't mean that I won't pull good out of it.

40:31.930 --> 40:34.573
I'm asking you to trust me again.

40:37.016 --> 40:41.862
I recently heard the story of a guy by the name of David Yubank who is raising his kids in a combat zone.

40:42.943 --> 40:49.170
He's a former Special Forces officer who assists as a medic and in rare instances will go into

40:49.794 --> 40:53.341
live firefights to pull out women and children who are in danger.

40:54.363 --> 40:59.652
He's got a 16 year old daughter who he says has driven an armored ambulance with him into these scenarios.

41:00.995 --> 41:01.736
And he said this.

41:02.478 --> 41:09.491
He goes, I never want to be in a position where I'm making decisions for my family that are born out of fear or comfort.

41:11.314 --> 41:13.298
And isn't that the great temptation for all of us?

41:14.978 --> 41:20.389
that we want safe, beautiful, accomplished families that are living comfortable and convenient lives.

41:21.892 --> 41:22.974
But I think God wants more.

41:24.477 --> 41:28.725
That God is calling us to a life of fierce faith and bold love.

41:28.745 --> 41:37.202
And just like God used Samson's family to remind them that even though they were having short-term heartache, God was using it for a broader impact.

41:37.986 --> 41:38.947
for a greater purpose.

41:38.967 --> 41:41.610
God wasn't just using one family for that family's journey.

41:41.671 --> 41:47.818
God was using that one family to affect the destiny of an entire town, a village, even in that particular, since a nation.

41:49.700 --> 41:59.092
So I think the challenge for many of us today, especially if we feel like our families don't look all that great when they're unfiltered, is to say, God, will you give us wisdom to zoom out and back?

42:00.414 --> 42:02.857
Will you give us perspective that we never would have had on our own?

42:02.897 --> 42:07.282
Will you show us how your hand, how your invisible hand is moving?

42:07.650 --> 42:19.285
to stretch us, to grow us, to mobilize us, and use us to bless other people for their good, even if it means we're feeling a little pinched and stretched right now.

42:20.506 --> 42:36.306
If your family journey isn't turning out the way that you wanted it to, don't be afraid, because God sees what you can, and God is going to leverage this season for your growth, God's glory, and others good.

42:37.698 --> 42:38.379
Let's pray together.

42:39.441 --> 42:43.649
Father God, I thank You that Your love for us is rich and true and real.

42:45.513 --> 42:59.058
And God, I thank You that Jesus' life, death, and resurrection promises us that You can redeem any hurt, any heartache, any degree of suffering so that we are conformed to Your image

42:59.586 --> 43:08.282
and that our gifts and our opportunities and our days are leveraged to advance your kingdom in ways that maybe only you can fully appreciate this side of eternity.

43:10.125 --> 43:21.485
In the meantime, Lord, give us faithfulness, give us perseverance to nacity, grit, and hope to live our lives in the direction that you're inviting us to live them.

43:21.505 --> 43:23.829
We pray these things in Christ's name.

43:23.849 --> 43:24.210
Amen.

52:06.114 --> 52:20.008
As we think about things that we can re-praise and God for, I wanted to let you know that just recently we had a mobile food pantry where we served over 8,000 pounds of food and 327 people in our community.

52:20.668 --> 52:26.734
When you give to Heritage Church with radical generosity, this is some of the things that you are a part of.

52:27.515 --> 52:34.802
So I'd encourage you to give with a cheerful heart through the Church Center app or through the HeritageQC.com website.

52:39.298 --> 52:43.842
We've been having some great conversations about our family life.

52:44.303 --> 52:52.551
And if you would like some more resources, you can go to the website, which is heritageqc.com, or talk to one of our family life pastors.

52:54.833 --> 52:58.357
Lastly, river baptism is coming up soon.

52:58.717 --> 53:00.899
And I am so excited for all of this.

53:01.380 --> 53:07.666
And if you feel like you're at the point where this is the right next step for you and live locally, I'd encourage you to sign up

53:07.906 --> 53:11.900
for River baptism, either through the Church Center app or through the website.

53:13.526 --> 53:17.138
For now, we'll look forward to seeing you guys here again next week.

